latestIgtvVideos.title: Our kids haven’t been to school in 2 years.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Dear Sirs,
As I’ve previously said, I’m so grateful for the protection and prompt action that we’ve received in Mumbai ….. we did well ! Thank you 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼 

But now we are pleading ….. don’t keep our schools shut any longer. Give us the choice. To send or not to send. PLEASE do this soon
 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

Children across the world have been in school for one whole year more than us. They too are fighting Omicron. 

It’s impacting our kids a LOT 😢

Also another message to ANY SCHOOL that didn’t want to open when the govt gave the go ahead last month …. SHAME ON YOU.

You’ve charged FULL FEES for two years. We’ve paid it. Some took loans to pay it.

And in 2 years if you couldn’t figure out your SOP’s and put education FIRST then you shouldn’t call yourself an educational institute !

I thank god for my school and so grateful for the constant effort they’re making to open doors when they get a go ahead.

Just give us the choice. It’s all we ask 🙏🏼

@openmumbaischoolsnow 

EVERY PERSON in this video willingly agreed to talk on camera and share their struggle.

@fayedsouza @barkha.dutt @officialhumansofbombay @indiatoday @rahulnarainkanal @iqchahal

latestPosts.caption:
The power of never giving up 😇🙌✨

Serena was exactly 4.9 years old when she got this NEW room. She’s currently 5.9 years.

Now let me tell you what mastering the monkey bars has done for my daughter -

1. Her confidence has peaked. She knows she can do this better than her older brother and all his friends. 🤍

2. Monkey bars provide a full-body workout, engaging multiple muscle groups and contributing to overall fitness and it’s CRUCIAL to ensure they are physically fit from the time they are young.

3. The act of swinging and moving across the bars improves hand-eye coordination, balance, and overall agility.

4. Their core strength, which is responsible for good body and brain function is at its peak.

5. Core strength exercises can positively impact brain function by improving balance, stability, and posture, and by stimulating brain areas that enhance movement control and cognitive function.

All in all, the physical and mental benefits of monkey bars are so epic !!!

So to ALLLL the haters who gave me grief on my post last year …. This is a reminder to get some sort of physical equipment into the house or garden if you have one. It is NOT a waste of money ! It’s a great investment in your child’s well being ! 😇🙏🏼😇🤍

Who agrees ?

And isn’t my little ninja awesome ??? 🥰🥹😇😇😇

I know you will ask so here goes - @letstickle.sensory did these bars for us ☺️

#momlife #motherhoodunplugged #monkeybars #motherhoodunfiltered

They call him “hands-on.” I just call him a parent.

Because bedtime isn’t “helping.” 
It’s parenting.

Equal parenting doesn’t mean that every single day our jobs are divided 50%.

It means one day Might be 80% me and 20% him and another day him 80 and me 20.

There are some cases where both parents work. There are some cases where it might be a stay at home mom who is drowning with her responsibilities while her husband is at work drowning with his own responsibilities.

Whatever the case is, time may never be found but time ALWAYS has to be made for parenting. Because we are EQUALLY their parents. 

Here’s to the partners who show up, no spotlight needed. 💡❤️

Who agrees ? 

#momlife #motherhoodunplugged #unfilteredmotherhood

I’m so proud of myself 🥰🥹

40 days clean !!!! 😇😇😇😇😇

Ok now let’s rewind.

I was a casual smoker in university when I lived in New York cause it was the cool thing to do. Little did I know it was the worst most stupid decision of my life.

I didn’t even realize when I got addicted and honestly my brother passing away triggered the addiction even more and it got even worse !!!

Ive been dying to quit. But I shunned the thought away every time cause I knew it was impossible. At least it felt impossible !!!

Obviously I quit through both my pregnancies and through the breastfeeding part, but that was NOT voluntary. The minute I started drinking again, boom, the smoking started again.

Then I turned 40 and I knew I HAD TO quit. I come from a family where in my paternal side addictive personalities are real. Some to Alcohol, some to nicotine, but the 
ONE THING I KNEW…..

Was that I HAD TO break the generational cycle. I just HAD to quit. So that this pattern never affects my kids. I had to do it for them.

And I did ! 😭😇😇

The friend I mentioned in the video is my earth angel @maliniagarwal who introduced me to the @quitsure.app !!!!

I promise you, I was a skeptic THROUGH THE ENTIRE PROGRAM.

I was like how the heck is an app going to make me quit. I mean what a joke.

But it did. With NO withdrawal symptoms, no anger, no frustration, just in the easiest manner possible 🤍🙏🏼

I don’t have much more space left in my caption to write more but I HIGHLY URGE YOU TO TRY THE @quitsure.app ! It’s worth EVERY PENNY. 

If it could work on an addict like ME, it can work on ANYYYYONEEEEEE ! 🤗🙏🏼😇

It’s truly the best best best thing out there !!!

I have NOTHING to gain from this at all other than blessings of even ONE of you quits through this. 

I owe SOOOOO MUCH to you Mals @maliniagarwal ! Thank you for making me download this and go through with it. Immensely grateful. 🤍🤍🤍

I INSIST that you research this for yourself !!!

But for now let’s learn a little about THESE ingredients -

Oxybenzone - 
This is an endocrine and hormone disrupter and it’s been banned in Hawai because it destroys coral and the EU has restricted its use since 2023.
However this is still present in MULTIPLE of the most popular sunscreen brands.

- Avobenzone

- Octinoxate

- Homosalate 

- Benzophenone

PLEASE DO YOUR RESEARCH ON THE ABOVE MENTIONED chemicals.

Other than those we obvious know that all Phthalates and Parabens are dangerous !!!

These too are present in multiple sunscreen brands.

The reason I ONLY pick @littleritualsindia is because I trust the brand completely and I trust their effort to truly provide one of the CLEANEST, SAFEST, kids skincare products in India.

You know I don’t lie. Especially when it comes to kids 🤍

Your sunscreen should be zinc and/or mineral based BUT some brands will promote it as zinc and mineral but will STILL have the nasties hidden in. 😅😭

The @littleritualsindia sunscreens are - 

✅Lightweight, non-sticky and leaves no white cast - which is a big ‘Yes’ for me.
✅ 100% Safe Ingredients, free from harmful chemicals & toxins
✅ MADE SAFE AUSTRALIA Certified 
✅Water-resistant, great to apply before swimming 
✅ They OffersBroad Spectrum UVA/UVB Protection
✅ Also protects against Bluelight, Wifi & Infrared Radiations

Sunscreen is crucial but using the RIGHT one matters the most.

It’s time to start reading and questioning skincare labels too, ESPECIALLY for our kids, right ???

Have you heard of these nasties before ?

If not I’m requesting you to research on them and then come back here and share your thoughts 🤍
